  "prompt": "How long can white wine last after it has been open?",
  "response": "The shelf life of an opened white wine depends on several factors, but generally:\n\n1. Refrigerated and recorked: Most white wines will last 3-5 days after opening if stored in the refrigerator with a cork or wine stopper.\n\n2. Sparkling white wines: These tend to go flat quickly and are best consumed within 1-2 days after opening.\n\n3. Higher quality or more complex white wines: These might last slightly longer, up to 5-7 days.\n\n4. Boxed white wines: These can last up to 4-6 weeks after opening due to their packaging design.\n\nTips to extend wine's life:\n- Always re-cork or use a wine stopper\n- Store in the refrigerator\n- Use a vacuum pump to remove excess air\n- Consume within a few days for best taste\n\nThe wine's taste will gradually deteriorate after opening, so it's best to drink it as soon as possible for optimal flavor.",
